						<summary>

						<p>Fragment. One of the fragments cites the 7th year (991-92 A.D.) of reign of <hi rend="bold">Rājarājakēsarivarman</hi> (i.e., <hi rend="bold">Rājarāja I</hi>) and mentions a certain Pallavaraiyaṉ of Paḻuvūr from whom some lands seem to have been bought. Another fragment refers to the deity Purushōttamattup-Perumāḷ. Two other fragments mention the deity Āṉaik[kāvil-Embe]rumāṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
